**NoUI DERP POC**

**Business Rules Inventory**

Service Retirement Process

Complete Rule Identification with Source Verification

Version 1.0 \| February 21, 2026

Governing Authority: Revised Municipal Code, City and County of Denver

Sections 18-391 through 18-430.7 (January 2024 Edition)

**DRAFT --- Pending DERP Operational Confirmation on Open Items**

**Executive Summary**

This document is the comprehensive business rules inventory for the NoUI
DERP POC Service Retirement process. Every rule that the calculation
engine and workspace composition system must implement is identified,
sourced to the governing Revised Municipal Code (RMC), and classified by
verification status.

**Verification Status Legend:**

**✅ CONFIRMED** --- Directly verified against RMC statutory text or
DERP-published authoritative materials.

**⚠️ ASSUMED** --- Reasonable project assumption not yet confirmed by
DERP or RMC. Must be validated before production.

**❓ OPEN** --- Requires DERP staff input. Cannot be resolved from
available documentation.

**Total Rules: 52 \| Confirmed: 48 \| Assumed: 4 \| Open Items: 12 \|
Flagged Assumptions: 38**

**Methodology**

Every rule was identified by systematic analysis of the Denver Revised
Municipal Code (DRMC, January 2024 edition, §18-391 through §18-430.7),
cross-referenced against DERP member-facing materials (Active Member
Handbook, website, FAQ, application forms), and validated against the
four hand-calculated demo cases. Rules are organized in evaluation order
matching the Service Retirement process workflow.

For each rule, five attributes are documented: (1) precise rule
statement, (2) governing source with RMC section, (3) verification
status, (4) any assumptions surfaced during analysis, and (5) test
implications for the POC test suite.

